      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% on the primary QoI at the production mesh level.",
      "rationale": "GCI of 3.1% on NIH at the fine-medium refinement level satisfies the 5% threshold. Richardson extrapolation was applied. Achieved level 3; required level 4 because absolute hemolysis threshold demands tighter numerical uncertainty bounds than relative comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
