      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI must be NIH or equivalent scalar hemolysis index directly comparable to the clinical threshold.",
      "rationale": "NIH is used as the primary QoI and is directly comparable to the clinical threshold. Secondary QoI (wall shear stress distribution) was reported but not used for the acceptance decision. Level 3 achieved; level 4 requires additional patient-population-specific hemolysis model validation not yet performed."
